      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.hIhgdXnqGHBm0A64]{Envoy Improvisation}</p>\n<p>@Icon[type:language-dependent] @Icon[type:mind-affecting] @Icon[type:sense-dependent]</p>\n<p>Your blistering battle rapport adds an extra sting to your attacks. The first time each round that you succeed at a weapon attack against a creature affected by your @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.TRq58BtMBgHi9dYc]{Vexing Style (Ex)}, you can choose to add your Charisma modifier to the attackâ€™s damage instead of adding your Strength modifier. If the attack would not normally add your Strength modifier to its damage, you instead add half your Charisma modifier as a bonus to the damage. You cannot apply your Charisma modifier to damage in this way with weapons that affect an area, such as those with the explode or line special weapon properties.</p>\n<p>You must have the vexing style improvisation to choose this improvisation.</p>"
